speaker: MARK ANTONY
text_entry: SCENE V. The same. Another room.

speaker: MARK ANTONY
text_entry: Enter DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS and EROS, meeting

speaker: DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS
text_entry: How now, friend Eros!

speaker: EROS
text_entry: There's strange news come, sir.

speaker: DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS
text_entry: What, man?

speaker: EROS
text_entry: Caesar and Lepidus have made wars upon Pompey.

speaker: DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS
text_entry: This is old: what is the success?

speaker: EROS
text_entry: Caesar, having made use of him in the wars 'gainst

speaker: EROS
text_entry: Pompey, presently denied him rivality; would not let

speaker: EROS
text_entry: him partake in the glory of the action: and not

speaker: EROS
text_entry: resting here, accuses him of letters he had formerly

speaker: EROS
text_entry: wrote to Pompey; upon his own appeal, seizes him: so

speaker: EROS
text_entry: the poor third is up, till death enlarge his confine.

speaker: DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS
text_entry: Then, world, thou hast a pair of chaps, no more;

speaker: DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS
text_entry: And throw between them all the food thou hast,

speaker: DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS
text_entry: They'll grind the one the other. Where's Antony?

speaker: EROS
text_entry: He's walking in the garden--thus; and spurns

speaker: EROS
text_entry: The rush that lies before him; cries, 'Fool Lepidus!'

speaker: EROS
text_entry: And threats the throat of that his officer

speaker: EROS
text_entry: That murder'd Pompey.

speaker: DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS
text_entry: Our great navy's rigg'd.

speaker: EROS
text_entry: For Italy and Caesar. More, Domitius;

speaker: EROS
text_entry: My lord desires you presently: my news

speaker: EROS
text_entry: I might have told hereafter.

speaker: DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS
text_entry: 'Twill be naught:

speaker: DOMITIUS ENOBARBUS
text_entry: But let it be. Bring me to Antony.

speaker: EROS
text_entry: Come, sir.

speaker: EROS
text_entry: Exeunt
